  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     Constitutional AI
Category:    Alignment
Definition:  AI trained on principles via self-critique to reduce harm
Year:        2022
Researchers: Anthropic/Bai et al.
Applications:Claude safety and alignment
Related:     RLHF, harmlessness, helpfulness, honesty

Concept:     Transfer Learning
Category:    Technique
Definition:  Reuses pre-trained model weights for new related tasks
Year:        2009
Researchers: Pan and Yang survey
Applications:Fine-tuning LLMs, computer vision
Related:     Pre-training, fine-tuning, domain adaptation

Concept:     Mixture of Experts
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Sparse model activating different expert subsets per token
Year:        2017
Researchers: Shazeer et al.
Applications:Large LLMs (Mixtral, rumored GPT-4)
Related:     Sparse activation, routing, scaling efficiency

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Stoicism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Focus only on what is in your control; accept all else with equanimity
Philosopher:  Marcus Aurelius/Epictetus
Example:      Illness is not in your control; your response to it is

Concept:      Existentialism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Existence precedes essence; radical freedom and responsibility
Philosopher:  Jean-Paul Sartre
Example:      You are not born kind or cruel; you become so through choices

Concept:      Rationalism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Some knowledge is innate or derivable by reason alone
Philosopher:  Descartes/Spinoza
Example:      Math truths like 2+2=4 are known by reason, not experiment

